{
  "note": "Labelled inner-agent eval scenarios (ADR-010 / F-05 criterion 8). Each scenario fixes an inbound event + learner snapshot and the expected tactical move family. The CI gate (≥95%) runs these through the real OpenAI provider when OPENAI_API_KEY is set; without a key the runner is skipped (see eval.test.ts). The heuristic provider is also asserted against the deterministic subset so the data stays honest offline. The `adversarial-*` scenarios target the brief's false-positive-mastery failure modes (over-scaffolding/hint-abuse, repeated guessing, scaffold-removal refusal, avoidance/off-topic deflection) — they assert the agent does NOT advance, reward, or hand a crutch to a learner exhibiting shallow success.",
