      "id": "adversarial-hint-abuse-ladder-exhausted-no-crutch",
      "note": "Over-scaffolding defense: a learner who has already drained all three hint levels on this item asks for a fourth. The agent must NOT hand another crutch — the ladder is exhausted (no_action), not silently re-served. (brief: 'Depend on hints or scaffolds')",
      "event": { "kind": "request_hint", "itemId": "l1-and" },
      "learnerState": { "consecutiveCorrect": 0, "hintsUsed": 3, "ruleGatePassed": false },
      "hintsByItem": { "l1-and": 3 },
      "expectMove": "no_action"
    },
    {
      "id": "adversarial-hint-abuse-last-rung-still-l3-not-advance",
      "note": "Over-scaffolding, mid-ladder: two hints already served on this item, a third request gets the LAST rung (L3) — never an advance/next item. Asking for help is not progress; the agent stays on remediation, not promotion.",
      "event": { "kind": "request_hint", "itemId": "l1-and" },
      "learnerState": { "consecutiveCorrect": 0, "hintsUsed": 2, "ruleGatePassed": false },
      "hintsByItem": { "l1-and": 2 },
      "expectMove": "propose_hint"
    },
    {
      "id": "adversarial-repeated-guessing-drops-to-simpler",
      "note": "Guessing defense: the learner already missed THIS item once and submits another wrong answer (cycling guesses). A repeated miss must drop to a SIMPLER item, never re-present the same one as if it were a fresh attempt — a guesser cannot grind the same item to a lucky pass. (brief: 'Guess correctly by luck')",
      "event": { "kind": "submit", "itemId": "l1-and", "submission": "A OR B", "correct": false },
      "learnerState": { "consecutiveCorrect": 0, "hintsUsed": 0, "ruleGatePassed": false },
      "priorMissesByItem": { "l1-and": 1 },
      "expectMove": "simpler_item"
    },
    {
      "id": "adversarial-no-hint-during-transfer-probe",
      "note": "Scaffold-removal defense: during a transfer probe (scaffolds removed) the learner requests a hint. The agent must REFUSE — no crutch during the transfer measurement, even if a stray affordance fired the request. A hint here would void the 'can they transfer without support?' signal. (brief: 'apply the skill ... with less scaffolding')",
      "event": { "kind": "request_hint", "itemId": "l1-and" },
      "learnerState": { "consecutiveCorrect": 3, "hintsUsed": 0, "ruleGatePassed": true },
      "inTransferProbe": true,
      "expectMove": "no_action"
    },
    {
      "id": "adversarial-avoidance-offtopic-deflected",
      "note": "Avoidance defense: a learner steering the tutor off-task to dodge the work. The agent classifies it off_topic and deflects back to the lesson rather than chasing the tangent. (brief: 'Click through without engaging' / avoidance)",
